<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-30">August 30,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Referring to Mr. Rockhill’s telegram of August 30, Mr. Adee instructs
                            him to make demand in accord with British, which is understood to be
                            that, until customs are established throughout Manchuria, no duties be
                            levied at Newchwang.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>